80static int idbKeyCollate(int aLength, const void* aBuffer, int bLength, const void* bBuffer)
81{
82 IDBKeyData a, b;
83 if (!deserializeIDBKeyData(static_cast<const uint8_t*>(aBuffer), aLength, a)) {
84 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key A in collation function.");
85
86 // There's no way to indicate an error to SQLite - we have to return a sorting decision.
87 // We arbitrarily choose "A > B"
88 return 1;
89 }
90 if (!deserializeIDBKeyData(static_cast<const uint8_t*>(bBuffer), bLength, b)) {
91 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key B in collation function.");
92
93 // There's no way to indicate an error to SQLite - we have to return a sorting decision.
94 // We arbitrarily choose "A > B"
95 return 1;
96 }
97
98 return a.compare(b);
99}

253static IDBError createOrMigrateRecordsTableIfNecessary(SQLiteDatabase& database)
254{
255 String tableStatement = database.tableSQL("Records"_s);
256 if (tableStatement.isEmpty()) {
257 if (!database.executeCommand(v3RecordsTableSchema()))
258 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating Records table (", database.lastError(), ") - ", database.lastErrorMsg()) };
259
260 return IDBError { };
261 }
262
263 // If the schema in the backing store is the current schema, we're done.
264 if (tableStatement == v3RecordsTableSchema() || tableStatement == v3RecordsTableSchemaAlternate())
265 return IDBError { };
266
267 // If the record table is not the current schema then it must be one of the previous schemas.
268 // If it is not then the database is in an unrecoverable state and this should be considered a fatal error.
269 if (tableStatement != v1RecordsTableSchema() && tableStatement != v1RecordsTableSchemaAlternate()
270 && tableStatement != v2RecordsTableSchema() && tableStatement != v2RecordsTableSchemaAlternate())
271 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
272
273 SQLiteTransaction transaction(database);
274 transaction.begin();
275
276 // Create a temporary table with the correct schema and migrate all existing content over.
277 if (!database.executeCommand(v3RecordsTableSchemaTemp()))
278 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating temporary Records table (", database.lastError(), ") - ", database.lastErrorMsg()) };
279
280 if (!database.executeCommand("INSERT INTO _Temp_Records (objectStoreID, key, value) SELECT objectStoreID, CAST(key AS TEXT), value FROM Records"_s))
281 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error migrating Records table (", database.lastError(), ") - ", database.lastErrorMsg()) };
282
283 if (!database.executeCommand("DROP TABLE Records"_s))
284 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error dropping Records table (", database.lastError(), ") - ", database.lastErrorMsg()) };
285
286 if (!database.executeCommand("ALTER TABLE _Temp_Records RENAME TO Records"_s))
287 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error renaming temporary Records table (", database.lastError(), ") - ", database.lastErrorMsg()) };
288
289 transaction.commit();
290
291 return IDBError { };
292}

294IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::ensureValidBlobTables()
295{
296 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
297 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
298
299 String recordsTableStatement = m_sqliteDB->tableSQL("BlobRecords"_s);
300 if (recordsTableStatement.isEmpty()) {
301 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand(blobRecordsTableSchema()))
302 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating BlobRecords table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
303
304 recordsTableStatement = blobRecordsTableSchema();
305 }
306
307 RELEASE_ASSERT(recordsTableStatement == blobRecordsTableSchema() || recordsTableStatement == blobRecordsTableSchemaAlternate());
308
309 String filesTableStatement = m_sqliteDB->tableSQL("BlobFiles"_s);
310 if (filesTableStatement.isEmpty()) {
311 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand(blobFilesTableSchema()))
312 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating BlobFiles table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
313
314 filesTableStatement = blobFilesTableSchema();
315 }
316
317 RELEASE_ASSERT(filesTableStatement == blobFilesTableSchema() || filesTableStatement == blobFilesTableSchemaAlternate());
318 return IDBError { };
319}

321IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::ensureValidRecordsTable()
322{
323 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
324 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
325
326 IDBError error = createOrMigrateRecordsTableIfNecessary(*m_sqliteDB);
327 if (!error.isNull())
328 return error;
329
330 // Whether the updated records table already existed or if it was just created and the data migrated over,
331 // make sure the uniqueness index exists.
332 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS RecordsIndex ON Records (objectStoreID, key);"_s))
333 error = IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating RecordsIndex on Records table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
334
335 return error;
336}

338IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::ensureValidIndexRecordsTable()
339{
340 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
341 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
342
343 String tableStatement = m_sqliteDB->tableSQL("IndexRecords"_s);
344 if (tableStatement.isEmpty()) {
345 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand(v3IndexRecordsTableSchema()))
346 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating IndexRecords table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
347
348 return IDBError { };
349 }
350
351 // If the schema in the backing store is the current schema, we're done.
352 if (tableStatement == v3IndexRecordsTableSchema() || tableStatement == v3IndexRecordsTableSchemaAlternate())
353 return IDBError { };
354
355 RELEASE_ASSERT(tableStatement == v1IndexRecordsTableSchema() || tableStatement == v1IndexRecordsTableSchemaAlternate() || tableStatement == v2IndexRecordsTableSchema() || tableStatement == v2IndexRecordsTableSchemaAlternate());
356
357 SQLiteTransaction transaction(*m_sqliteDB);
358 transaction.begin();
359
360 // Create a temporary table with the correct schema and migrate all existing content over.
361 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand(v3IndexRecordsTableSchemaTemp()))
362 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error creating temporary IndexRecords table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
363
364 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("INSERT INTO _Temp_IndexRecords SELECT IndexRecords.indexID, IndexRecords.objectStoreID, IndexRecords.key, IndexRecords.value, Records.rowid FROM IndexRecords INNER JOIN Records ON Records.key = IndexRecords.value AND Records.objectStoreID = IndexRecords.objectStoreID"_s))
365 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error migrating IndexRecords table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
366
367 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("DROP TABLE IndexRecords"_s))
368 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error dropping IndexRecords table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
369
370 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("ALTER TABLE _Temp_IndexRecords RENAME TO IndexRecords"_s))
371 return IDBError { UnknownError, makeString("Error renaming temporary IndexRecords table (", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), ") - ", m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg()) };
372
373 transaction.commit();
374
375 return IDBError { };
376}

414std::unique_ptr<IDBDatabaseInfo> SQLiteIDBBackingStore::createAndPopulateInitialDatabaseInfo()
415{
416 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
417 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
418
419 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("CREATE TABLE IDBDatabaseInfo (key TEXT NOT NULL ON CONFLICT FAIL UNIQUE ON CONFLICT REPLACE, value TEXT NOT NULL ON CONFLICT FAIL);"_s)) {
420 LOG_ERROR("Could not create IDBDatabaseInfo table in database (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
421 closeSQLiteDB();
422 return nullptr;
423 }
424
425 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand(v2ObjectStoreInfoSchema)) {
426 LOG_ERROR("Could not create ObjectStoreInfo table in database (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
427 closeSQLiteDB();
428 return nullptr;
429 }
430
431 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand(indexInfoTableSchema())) {
432 LOG_ERROR("Could not create IndexInfo table in database (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
433 closeSQLiteDB();
434 return nullptr;
435 }
436
437 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("CREATE TABLE KeyGenerators (objectStoreID INTEGER NOT NULL ON CONFLICT FAIL UNIQUE ON CONFLICT REPLACE, currentKey INTEGER NOT NULL ON CONFLICT FAIL);"_s)) {
438 LOG_ERROR("Could not create KeyGenerators table in database (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
439 closeSQLiteDB();
440 return nullptr;
441 }
442
443 {
444 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("INSERT INTO IDBDatabaseInfo VALUES ('MetadataVersion', ?);"_s);
445 if (!sql
446 || sql->bindInt(1, currentMetadataVersion) != SQLITE_OK
447 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
448 LOG_ERROR("Could not insert database metadata version into IDBDatabaseInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
449 closeSQLiteDB();
450 return nullptr;
451 }
452 }
453 {
454 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("INSERT INTO IDBDatabaseInfo VALUES ('DatabaseName', ?);"_s);
455 if (!sql
456 || sql->bindText(1, m_identifier.databaseName()) != SQLITE_OK
457 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
458 LOG_ERROR("Could not insert database name into IDBDatabaseInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
459 closeSQLiteDB();
460 return nullptr;
461 }
462 }
463 {
464 // Database versions are defined to be a uin64_t in the spec but sqlite3 doesn't support native binding of unsigned integers.
465 // Therefore we'll store the version as a String.
466 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("INSERT INTO IDBDatabaseInfo VALUES ('DatabaseVersion', ?);"_s);
467 if (!sql
468 || sql->bindText(1, String::number(0)) != SQLITE_OK
469 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
470 LOG_ERROR("Could not insert default version into IDBDatabaseInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
471 closeSQLiteDB();
472 return nullptr;
473 }
474 }
475
476 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("INSERT INTO IDBDatabaseInfo VALUES ('MaxObjectStoreID', 1);"_s)) {
477 LOG_ERROR("Could not insert default version into IDBDatabaseInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
478 closeSQLiteDB();
479 return nullptr;
480 }
481
482 // This initial database info matches the default values we just put into the metadata database.
483 return makeUnique<IDBDatabaseInfo>(m_identifier.databaseName(), 0, 0);
484}
485
486std::optional<IsSchemaUpgraded> SQLiteIDBBackingStore::ensureValidObjectStoreInfoTable()
487{
488 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
489 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
490
491 String tableStatement = m_sqliteDB->tableSQL("ObjectStoreInfo"_s);
492 if (tableStatement.isEmpty())
493 return std::nullopt;
494
495 if (tableStatement == v2ObjectStoreInfoSchema || tableStatement == createV2ObjectStoreInfoSchema(objectStoreInfoTableNameAlternate))
496 return { IsSchemaUpgraded::No };
497
498 RELEASE_ASSERT(tableStatement == createV1ObjectStoreInfoSchema(objectStoreInfoTableName) || tableStatement == createV1ObjectStoreInfoSchema(objectStoreInfoTableNameAlternate));
499
500 // Drop column maxIndexID from table.
501 SQLiteTransaction transaction(*m_sqliteDB);
502 transaction.begin();
503
504 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommandSlow(createV2ObjectStoreInfoSchema("_Temp_ObjectStoreInfo"_s))) {
505 LOG_ERROR("Could not create temporary ObjectStoreInfo table in database (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
506 return std::nullopt;
507 }
508
509 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("INSERT INTO _Temp_ObjectStoreInfo (id, name, keyPath, autoInc) SELECT id, name, keyPath, autoInc FROM ObjectStoreInfo"_s)) {
510 LOG_ERROR("Could not migrate existing ObjectStoreInfo content (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
511 return std::nullopt;
512 }
513
514 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("DROP TABLE ObjectStoreInfo"_s)) {
515 LOG_ERROR("Could not drop existing ObjectStoreInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
516 return std::nullopt;
517 }
518
519 if (!m_sqliteDB->executeCommand("ALTER TABLE _Temp_ObjectStoreInfo RENAME TO ObjectStoreInfo"_s)) {
520 LOG_ERROR("Could not rename temporary ObjectStoreInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
521 return std::nullopt;
522 }
523
524 transaction.commit();
525
526 return { IsSchemaUpgraded::Yes };
527}
528
529bool SQLiteIDBBackingStore::migrateIndexInfoTableForIDUpdate(const HashMap<std::pair<uint64_t, uint64_t>, uint64_t>& indexIDMap)
530{
531 SQLiteDatabase& database = *m_sqliteDB;
532 SQLiteTransaction transaction(database);
533 transaction.begin();
534
535 if (!database.executeCommand(indexInfoTableSchemaTemp())) {
536 LOG_ERROR("Error creating _Temp_IndexInfo table in database (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
537 return false;
538 }
539
540 {
541 auto statement = database.prepareStatement("SELECT id, name, objectStoreID, keyPath, isUnique, multiEntry FROM IndexInfo;"_s);
542 if (!statement) {
543 LOG_ERROR("Error preparing statement to fetch records from IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
544 return false;
545 }
546
547 int result = statement->step();
548 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
549 uint64_t id = statement->columnInt64(0);
550 String name = statement->columnText(1);
551 uint64_t objectStoreID = statement->columnInt64(2);
552 uint64_t newID = indexIDMap.get({ objectStoreID, id });
553 auto keyPathBufferSpan = statement->columnBlobAsSpan(3);
554 bool unique = statement->columnInt(4);
555 bool multiEntry = statement->columnInt(5);
556
557 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::CreateTempIndexInfo, "INSERT INTO _Temp_IndexInfo VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?);"_s);
558 if (!sql
559 || sql->bindInt64(1, newID) != SQLITE_OK
560 || sql->bindText(2, name) != SQLITE_OK
561 || sql->bindInt64(3, objectStoreID) != SQLITE_OK
562 || sql->bindBlob(4, keyPathBufferSpan) != SQLITE_OK
563 || sql->bindInt(5, unique) != SQLITE_OK
564 || sql->bindInt(6, multiEntry) != SQLITE_OK
565 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
566 LOG_ERROR("Error adding index '%s' to _Temp_IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", name.utf8().data(), database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
567 return false;
568 }
569
570 result = statement->step();
571 }
572
573 if (result != SQLITE_DONE) {
574 LOG_ERROR("Error fetching indices from IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
575 return false;
576 }
577 }
578
579 if (!database.executeCommand("DROP TABLE IndexInfo"_s)) {
580 LOG_ERROR("Error dropping existing IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
581 return false;
582 }
583
584 if (!database.executeCommand("ALTER TABLE _Temp_IndexInfo RENAME TO IndexInfo"_s)) {
585 LOG_ERROR("Error renaming _Temp_IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
586 return false;
587 }
588
589 transaction.commit();
590 return true;
591}
592
593bool SQLiteIDBBackingStore::migrateIndexRecordsTableForIDUpdate(const HashMap<std::pair<uint64_t, uint64_t>, uint64_t>& indexIDMap)
594{
595 SQLiteDatabase& database = *m_sqliteDB;
596 SQLiteTransaction transaction(database);
597 transaction.begin();
598
599 if (!database.executeCommand(v3IndexRecordsTableSchemaTemp())) {
600 LOG_ERROR("Error creating _Temp_IndexRecords table in database (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
601 return false;
602 }
603
604 {
605 auto statement = database.prepareStatement("SELECT indexID, objectStoreID, key, value, objectStoreRecordID FROM IndexRecords;"_s);
606 if (!statement) {
607 LOG_ERROR("Error preparing statement to fetch records from the IndexRecords table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
608 return false;
609 }
610
611 int result = statement->step();
612 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
613 uint64_t id = statement->columnInt64(0);
614 uint64_t objectStoreID = statement->columnInt64(1);
615 uint64_t newID = indexIDMap.get({ objectStoreID, id });
616 auto keyBufferSpan = statement->columnBlobAsSpan(2);
617 auto valueBufferSpan = statement->columnBlobAsSpan(3);
618 uint64_t recordID = statement->columnInt64(4);
619
620 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::PutTempIndexRecord, "INSERT INTO _Temp_IndexRecords VALUES (?, ?, CAST(? AS TEXT), CAST(? AS TEXT), ?);"_s);
621 if (!sql
622 || sql->bindInt64(1, newID) != SQLITE_OK
623 || sql->bindInt64(2, objectStoreID) != SQLITE_OK
624 || sql->bindBlob(3, keyBufferSpan) != SQLITE_OK
625 || sql->bindBlob(4, valueBufferSpan) != SQLITE_OK
626 || sql->bindInt64(5, recordID) != SQLITE_OK
627 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
628 LOG_ERROR("Error adding index record to _Temp_IndexRecords table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
629 return false;
630 }
631
632 result = statement->step();
633 }
634
635 if (result != SQLITE_DONE) {
636 LOG_ERROR("Error fetching index record from database on disk (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
637 return false;
638 }
639 }
640
641 if (!database.executeCommand("DROP TABLE IndexRecords"_s)) {
642 LOG_ERROR("Error dropping existing IndexRecords table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
643 return false;
644 }
645
646 if (!database.executeCommand("ALTER TABLE _Temp_IndexRecords RENAME TO IndexRecords"_s)) {
647 LOG_ERROR("Error renaming temporary IndexRecords table (%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
648 return false;
649 }
650
651 transaction.commit();
652 return true;
653}
654
655bool SQLiteIDBBackingStore::removeExistingIndex(uint64_t indexID)
656{
657 SQLiteTransaction transaction(*m_sqliteDB);
658 transaction.begin();
659
660 {
661 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::RemoveIndexInfo, "DELETE FROM IndexInfo WHERE id = ?;"_s);
662 if (!sql
663 || sql->bindInt64(1, indexID) != SQLITE_OK
664 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
665 LOG_ERROR("Unable to remove existing index from IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
666 return false;
667 }
668 }
669
670 {
671 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteIndexRecords, "DELETE FROM IndexRecords WHERE indexID = ?;"_s);
672 if (!sql
673 || sql->bindInt64(1, indexID) != SQLITE_OK
674 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
675 LOG_ERROR("Unable to remove existing index from IndexRecords table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
676 return false;
677 }
678 }
679
680 transaction.commit();
681 return true;
682}
683
684bool SQLiteIDBBackingStore::addExistingIndex(IDBObjectStoreInfo& objectStoreInfo, const IDBIndexInfo& info)
685{
686 SQLiteTransaction transaction(*m_sqliteDB);
687 transaction.begin();
688
689 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> keyPathBlob = serializeIDBKeyPath(info.keyPath());
690 if (!keyPathBlob) {
691 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize IDBKeyPath to save in database");
692 return false;
693 }
694
695 {
696 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::CreateIndexInfo, "INSERT INTO IndexInfo VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?);"_s);
697 if (!sql
698 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
699 || sql->bindText(2, info.name()) != SQLITE_OK
700 || sql->bindInt64(3, info.objectStoreIdentifier()) != SQLITE_OK
701 || sql->bindBlob(4, *keyPathBlob) != SQLITE_OK
702 || sql->bindInt(5, info.unique()) != SQLITE_OK
703 || sql->bindInt(6, info.multiEntry()) != SQLITE_OK
704 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
705 LOG_ERROR("Could not add index '%s' to IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", info.name().utf8().data(), m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
706 return false;
707 }
708 }
709
710 {
711 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetObjectStoreRecords, "SELECT key, value, recordID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ?;"_s);
712 if (!sql
713 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.objectStoreIdentifier()) != SQLITE_OK) {
714 LOG_ERROR("Unable to prepare statement or bind values (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
715 return false;
716 }
717
718 int result = sql->step();
719 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
720 auto keyBufferSpan = sql->columnBlobAsSpan(0);
721 IDBKeyData keyData;
722 if (!deserializeIDBKeyData(keyBufferSpan.data(), keyBufferSpan.size(), keyData)) {
723 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key data from database while getting all records");
724 return false;
725 }
726
727 auto value = ThreadSafeDataBuffer::create(sql->columnBlob(1));
728
729 uint64_t recordID = sql->columnInt64(2);
730 IDBError error = updateOneIndexForAddRecord(objectStoreInfo, info, keyData, value, recordID);
731 if (!error.isNull())
732 return false;
733
734 result = sql->step();
735 }
736
737 if (result != SQLITE_DONE) {
738 LOG_ERROR("Error fetching object records from Records table on disk");
739 return false;
740 }
741 }
742
743 transaction.commit();
744 return true;
745}
746
747bool SQLiteIDBBackingStore::handleDuplicateIndexIDs(const HashMap<uint64_t, Vector<IDBIndexInfo>>& indexInfoMap, IDBDatabaseInfo& databaseInfo)
748{
749 for (auto& iter : indexInfoMap) {
750 if (iter.value.size() == 1)
751 continue;
752
753 if (!removeExistingIndex(iter.key))
754 return false;
755
756 for (auto info : iter.value) {
757 auto objectStoreInfo = databaseInfo.infoForExistingObjectStore(info.objectStoreIdentifier());
758 ASSERT(objectStoreInfo);
759 objectStoreInfo->deleteIndex(info.identifier());
760
761 // A new index with the same name may already be added.
762 if (objectStoreInfo->hasIndex(info.name()))
763 continue;
764
765 info.setIdentifier(databaseInfo.generateNextIndexID());
766 if (!addExistingIndex(*objectStoreInfo, info))
767 return false;
768
769 objectStoreInfo->addExistingIndex(info);
770 }
771 }
772
773 return true;
774}
775
776std::unique_ptr<IDBDatabaseInfo> SQLiteIDBBackingStore::extractExistingDatabaseInfo()
777{
778 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
779
780 if (!m_sqliteDB->tableExists("IDBDatabaseInfo"_s))
781 return nullptr;
782
783 String databaseName;
784 {
785 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("SELECT value FROM IDBDatabaseInfo WHERE key = 'DatabaseName';"_s);
786 databaseName = sql->columnText(0);
787 if (databaseName != m_identifier.databaseName()) {
788 LOG_ERROR("Database name in the info database ('%s') does not match the expected name ('%s')", databaseName.utf8().data(), m_identifier.databaseName().utf8().data());
789 return nullptr;
790 }
791 }
792 uint64_t databaseVersion;
793 {
794 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("SELECT value FROM IDBDatabaseInfo WHERE key = 'DatabaseVersion';"_s);
795 String stringVersion = sql->columnText(0);
796 auto parsedVersion = parseInteger<uint64_t>(stringVersion);
797 if (!parsedVersion) {
798 LOG_ERROR("Database version on disk ('%s') does not cleanly convert to an unsigned 64-bit integer version", stringVersion.utf8().data());
799 return nullptr;
800 }
801 databaseVersion = *parsedVersion;
802 }
803
804 auto databaseInfo = makeUnique<IDBDatabaseInfo>(databaseName, databaseVersion, 0);
805
806 auto result = ensureValidObjectStoreInfoTable();
807 if (!result)
808 return nullptr;
809
810 bool shouldUpdateIndexID = (result.value() == IsSchemaUpgraded::Yes);
811
812 {
813 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("SELECT id, name, keyPath, autoInc FROM ObjectStoreInfo;"_s);
814 if (!sql)
815 return nullptr;
816
817 int result = sql->step();
818 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
819 uint64_t objectStoreID = sql->columnInt64(0);
820 String objectStoreName = sql->columnText(1);
821 auto keyPathBufferSpan = sql->columnBlobAsSpan(2);
822
823 std::optional<IDBKeyPath> objectStoreKeyPath;
824 if (!deserializeIDBKeyPath(keyPathBufferSpan.data(), keyPathBufferSpan.size(), objectStoreKeyPath)) {
825 LOG_ERROR("Unable to extract key path from database");
826 return nullptr;
827 }
828
829 bool autoIncrement = sql->columnInt(3);
830
831 databaseInfo->addExistingObjectStore({ objectStoreID, objectStoreName, WTFMove(objectStoreKeyPath), autoIncrement });
832
833 result = sql->step();
834 }
835
836 if (result != SQLITE_DONE) {
837 LOG_ERROR("Error fetching object store info from database on disk");
838 return nullptr;
839 }
840 }
841
842 uint64_t maxIndexID = 0;
843 HashMap<std::pair<uint64_t, uint64_t>, uint64_t> indexIDMap;
844 HashMap<uint64_t, Vector<IDBIndexInfo>> indexInfoMap;
845 {
846 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("SELECT id, name, objectStoreID, keyPath, isUnique, multiEntry FROM IndexInfo;"_s);
847 if (!sql) {
848 LOG_ERROR("Unable to prepare statement to fetch records from the IndexInfo table.");
849 return nullptr;
850 }
851
852 int result = sql->step();
853 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
854 uint64_t indexID = sql->columnInt64(0);
855 String indexName = sql->columnText(1);
856 uint64_t objectStoreID = sql->columnInt64(2);
857 auto keyPathBufferSpan = sql->columnBlobAsSpan(3);
858
859 std::optional<IDBKeyPath> indexKeyPath;
860 if (!deserializeIDBKeyPath(keyPathBufferSpan.data(), keyPathBufferSpan.size(), indexKeyPath)) {
861 LOG_ERROR("Unable to extract key path from database");
862 return nullptr;
863 }
864 if (!indexKeyPath) {
865 LOG_ERROR("Unable to extract key path from database");
866 return nullptr;
867 }
868
869 bool unique = sql->columnInt(4);
870 bool multiEntry = sql->columnInt(5);
871
872 auto objectStore = databaseInfo->infoForExistingObjectStore(objectStoreID);
873 if (!objectStore) {
874 LOG_ERROR("Found index referring to a non-existant object store");
875 return nullptr;
876 }
877
878 if (shouldUpdateIndexID) {
879 indexIDMap.set({ objectStoreID, indexID }, ++maxIndexID);
880 indexID = maxIndexID;
881 }
882
883 auto indexInfo = IDBIndexInfo { indexID, objectStoreID, indexName, WTFMove(indexKeyPath.value()), unique, multiEntry };
884 if (!shouldUpdateIndexID) {
885 auto& indexInfos = indexInfoMap.ensure(indexID, []() -> Vector<IDBIndexInfo> {
886 return { };
887 }).iterator->value;
888 indexInfos.append(indexInfo);
889 }
890
891 objectStore->addExistingIndex(indexInfo);
892 maxIndexID = maxIndexID < indexID ? indexID : maxIndexID;
893
894 result = sql->step();
895 }
896
897 if (result != SQLITE_DONE) {
898 LOG_ERROR("Error fetching index info from database on disk");
899 return nullptr;
900 }
901 databaseInfo->setMaxIndexID(maxIndexID);
902 }
903
904 if (shouldUpdateIndexID) {
905 if (!migrateIndexInfoTableForIDUpdate(indexIDMap) || !migrateIndexRecordsTableForIDUpdate(indexIDMap))
906 return nullptr;
907 } else {
908 if (!handleDuplicateIndexIDs(indexInfoMap, *databaseInfo))
909 return nullptr;
910 }
911
912 return databaseInfo;
913}

923 filename.replace('.', "%2E");

937
938std::optional<IDBDatabaseNameAndVersion> SQLiteIDBBackingStore::databaseNameAndVersionFromFile(const String& databasePath)
939{
940 SQLiteDatabase database;
941 if (!database.open(databasePath)) {
942 LOG_ERROR("Failed to open SQLite database at path '%s' when getting database name", databasePath.utf8().data());
943 return std::nullopt;
944 }
945 if (!database.tableExists("IDBDatabaseInfo"_s)) {
946 LOG_ERROR("Could not find IDBDatabaseInfo table and get database name(%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
947 return std::nullopt;
948 }
949
950 auto namesql = database.prepareStatement("SELECT value FROM IDBDatabaseInfo WHERE key = 'DatabaseName';"_s);
951 if (!namesql) {
952 LOG_ERROR("Could not prepare statement to get database name(%i) - %s", database.lastError(), database.lastErrorMsg());
953 return std::nullopt;
954 }
955 auto databaseName = namesql->columnText(0);
956
957 auto versql = database.prepareStatement("SELECT value FROM IDBDatabaseInfo WHERE key = 'DatabaseVersion';"_s);
958 String stringVersion = versql ? versql->columnText(0) : String();
959 auto databaseVersion = parseInteger<uint64_t>(stringVersion);
960 if (!databaseVersion) {
961 LOG_ERROR("Database version on disk ('%s') does not cleanly convert to an unsigned 64-bit integer version", stringVersion.utf8().data());
962 return std::nullopt;
963 }
964
965 return IDBDatabaseNameAndVersion { databaseName, *databaseVersion };
966}
967
968String SQLiteIDBBackingStore::fullDatabaseDirectoryWithUpgrade()
969{
970 String oldOriginDirectory = m_identifier.databaseDirectoryRelativeToRoot(m_databaseRootDirectory, "v0");
971 String oldDatabaseDirectory = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(oldOriginDirectory, filenameForDatabaseName());
972 String newOriginDirectory = m_identifier.databaseDirectoryRelativeToRoot(m_databaseRootDirectory, "v1");
973 String fileNameHash = SQLiteFileSystem::computeHashForFileName(m_identifier.databaseName());
974 String newDatabaseDirectory = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(newOriginDirectory, fileNameHash);
975 FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(newDatabaseDirectory);
976
977 if (FileSystem::fileExists(oldDatabaseDirectory)) {
978 FileSystem::moveFile(oldDatabaseDirectory, newDatabaseDirectory);
979 FileSystem::deleteEmptyDirectory(oldOriginDirectory);
980 }
981
982 return newDatabaseDirectory;
983}
984
985IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getOrEstablishDatabaseInfo(IDBDatabaseInfo& info)
986{
987 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getOrEstablishDatabaseInfo - database %s", m_identifier.databaseName().utf8().data());
988
989 if (m_databaseInfo) {
990 info = *m_databaseInfo;
991 return IDBError { };
992 }
993
994 String dbFilename = fullDatabasePath();
995
996 m_sqliteDB = makeUnique<SQLiteDatabase>();
997 if (!m_sqliteDB->open(dbFilename)) {
998 LOG_ERROR("Failed to open SQLite database at path '%s'", dbFilename.utf8().data());
999 closeSQLiteDB();
1000 }
1001
1002 if (!m_sqliteDB)
1003 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to open database file on disk"_s };
1004
1005 m_sqliteDB->disableThreadingChecks();
1006 m_sqliteDB->enableAutomaticWALTruncation();
1007
1008 m_sqliteDB->setCollationFunction("IDBKEY", [](int aLength, const void* a, int bLength, const void* b) {
1009 return idbKeyCollate(aLength, a, bLength, b);
1010 });
1011
1012 IDBError error = ensureValidRecordsTable();
1013 if (!error.isNull()) {
1014 closeSQLiteDB();
1015 return error;
1016 }
1017
1018 error = ensureValidIndexRecordsTable();
1019 if (!error.isNull()) {
1020 closeSQLiteDB();
1021 return error;
1022 }
1023
1024 error = ensureValidIndexRecordsIndex();
1025 if (!error.isNull()) {
1026 closeSQLiteDB();
1027 return error;
1028 }
1029
1030 error = ensureValidIndexRecordsRecordIndex();
1031 if (!error.isNull()) {
1032 closeSQLiteDB();
1033 return error;
1034 }
1035
1036 error = ensureValidBlobTables();
1037 if (!error.isNull()) {
1038 closeSQLiteDB();
1039 return error;
1040 }
1041
1042 auto databaseInfo = extractExistingDatabaseInfo();
1043 if (!databaseInfo)
1044 databaseInfo = createAndPopulateInitialDatabaseInfo();
1045
1046 if (!databaseInfo) {
1047 LOG_ERROR("Unable to establish IDB database at path '%s'", dbFilename.utf8().data());
1048 closeSQLiteDB();
1049 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to establish IDB database file"_s };
1050 }
1051
1052 m_databaseInfo = WTFMove(databaseInfo);
1053 info = *m_databaseInfo;
1054 return IDBError { };
1055}
1056
1057uint64_t SQLiteIDBBackingStore::databaseVersion()
1058{
1059 if (m_databaseInfo)
1060 return m_databaseInfo->version();
1061
1062 String dbFilename = fullDatabasePath();
1063 if (!FileSystem::fileExists(dbFilename))
1064 return 0;
1065
1066 auto databaseNameAndVersion = databaseNameAndVersionFromFile(dbFilename);
1067 return databaseNameAndVersion ? databaseNameAndVersion->version : 0;
1068}

1070uint64_t SQLiteIDBBackingStore::databasesSizeForDirectory(const String& directory)
1071{
1072 uint64_t diskUsage = 0;
1073 for (auto& dbDirectoryName : FileSystem::listDirectory(directory)) {
1074 auto dbDirectoryPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(directory, dbDirectoryName);
1075 for (auto& fileName : FileSystem::listDirectory(dbDirectoryPath)) {

1082
1083IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::beginTransaction(const IDBTransactionInfo& info)
1084{
1085 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::beginTransaction - %s", info.identifier().loggingString().utf8().data());
1086
1087 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1088 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1089 ASSERT(m_databaseInfo);
1090
1091 auto addResult = m_transactions.add(info.identifier(), nullptr);
1092 if (!addResult.isNewEntry) {
1093 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to establish transaction identifier that already exists");
1094 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to establish transaction identifier that already exists"_s };
1095 }
1096
1097 addResult.iterator->value = makeUnique<SQLiteIDBTransaction>(*this, info);
1098
1099 auto error = addResult.iterator->value->begin(*m_sqliteDB);
1100 if (error.isNull() && info.mode() == IDBTransactionMode::Versionchange) {
1101 m_originalDatabaseInfoBeforeVersionChange = makeUnique<IDBDatabaseInfo>(*m_databaseInfo);
1102
1103 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("UPDATE IDBDatabaseInfo SET value = ? where key = 'DatabaseVersion';"_s);
1104 if (!sql
1105 || sql->bindText(1, String::number(info.newVersion())) != SQLITE_OK
1106 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1107 error = IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to store new database version in database"_s };
1108 }
1109 }
1110
1111 return error;
1112}
1113
1114IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::abortTransaction(const IDBResourceIdentifier& identifier)
1115{
1116 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::abortTransaction - %s", identifier.loggingString().utf8().data());
1117
1118 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1119 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1120
1121 auto transaction = m_transactions.take(identifier);
1122 if (!transaction) {
1123 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to commit a transaction that hasn't been established");
1124 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to abort a transaction that hasn't been established"_s };
1125 }
1126
1127 if (transaction->mode() == IDBTransactionMode::Versionchange && m_originalDatabaseInfoBeforeVersionChange)
1128 m_databaseInfo = WTFMove(m_originalDatabaseInfoBeforeVersionChange);
1129
1130 return transaction->abort();
1131}
1132
1133IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::commitTransaction(const IDBResourceIdentifier& identifier)
1134{
1135 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::commitTransaction - %s", identifier.loggingString().utf8().data());
1136
1137 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1138 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1139
1140 auto transaction = m_transactions.take(identifier);
1141 if (!transaction) {
1142 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to commit a transaction that hasn't been established");
1143 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to commit a transaction that hasn't been established"_s };
1144 }
1145
1146 auto error = transaction->commit();
1147 if (!error.isNull()) {
1148 if (transaction->mode() == IDBTransactionMode::Versionchange) {
1149 ASSERT(m_originalDatabaseInfoBeforeVersionChange);
1150 m_databaseInfo = WTFMove(m_originalDatabaseInfoBeforeVersionChange);
1151 }
1152 } else
1153 m_originalDatabaseInfoBeforeVersionChange = nullptr;
1154
1155 return error;
1156}
1157
1158IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::createObjectStore(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, const IDBObjectStoreInfo& info)
1159{
1160 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::createObjectStore - adding OS %s with ID %" PRIu64, info.name().utf8().data(), info.identifier());
1161
1162 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1163 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1164
1165 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
1166 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
1167 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to create an object store without an in-progress transaction"_s };
1168
1169 if (transaction->mode() != IDBTransactionMode::Versionchange) {
1170 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to create an object store in a non-version-change transaction");
1171 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to create an object store in a non-version-change transaction"_s };
1172 }
1173
1174 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> keyPathBlob = serializeIDBKeyPath(info.keyPath());
1175 if (!keyPathBlob) {
1176 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize IDBKeyPath to save in database for new object store");
1177 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize IDBKeyPath to save in database for new object store"_s };
1178 }
1179
1180 {
1181 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::CreateObjectStoreInfo, "INSERT INTO ObjectStoreInfo VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?);"_s);
1182 if (!sql
1183 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1184 || sql->bindText(2, info.name()) != SQLITE_OK
1185 || sql->bindBlob(3, *keyPathBlob) != SQLITE_OK
1186 || sql->bindInt(4, info.autoIncrement()) != SQLITE_OK
1187 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1188 LOG_ERROR("Could not add object store '%s' to ObjectStoreInfo table (%i) - %s", info.name().utf8().data(), m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1189 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Could not create object store"_s };
1190 }
1191 }
1192
1193 {
1194 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::CreateObjectStoreKeyGenerator, "INSERT INTO KeyGenerators VALUES (?, 0);"_s);
1195 if (!sql
1196 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1197 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1198 LOG_ERROR("Could not seed initial key generator value for ObjectStoreInfo table (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1199 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Could not seed initial key generator value for object store"_s };
1200 }
1201 }
1202
1203 m_databaseInfo->addExistingObjectStore(info);
1204
1205 return IDBError { };

1208IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteObjectStore(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, uint64_t objectStoreIdentifier)
1209{
1210 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteObjectStore - object store %" PRIu64, objectStoreIdentifier);
1211
1212 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1213 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1214
1215 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
1216 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
1217 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to delete an object store without an in-progress transaction"_s };
1218

1222 }

1224 // Delete the ObjectStore record
1225 {
1226 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreInfo, "DELETE FROM ObjectStoreInfo WHERE id = ?;"_s);
1227 if (!sql
1228 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK
1229 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {

1231 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Could not delete object store"_s };
1232 }
1233 }
1234
1235 // Delete the ObjectStore's key generator record if there is one.
1236 {
1237 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreKeyGenerator, "DELETE FROM KeyGenerators WHERE objectStoreID = ?;"_s);
1238 if (!sql
1239 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK
1240 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {

1244 }

1246 // Delete all associated records
1247 {
1248 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreRecords, "DELETE FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ?;"_s);
1249 if (!sql
1250 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK
1251 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1252 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete records for object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) - %s", objectStoreIdentifier, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());

1260 if (!sql
1261 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK

1276 }
1277 }
1278
1279 // Delete all unused Blob URL records.
1280 {
1281 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreBlobRecords, "DELETE FROM BlobRecords WHERE objectStoreRow NOT IN (SELECT recordID FROM Records)"_s);
1282 if (!sql
1283 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1284 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete Blob URL records(%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1285 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Could not delete stored blob records for deleted object store"_s };
1286 }
1287 }
1288
1289 // Delete all unused Blob File records.
1290 auto error = deleteUnusedBlobFileRecords(*transaction);
1291 if (!error.isNull())
1292 return error;

1294 m_databaseInfo->deleteObjectStore(objectStoreIdentifier);
1295
1296 return IDBError { };

1371
1372IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::createIndex(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, const IDBIndexInfo& info)
1373{
1374 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::createIndex - ObjectStore %" PRIu64 ", Index %" PRIu64, info.objectStoreIdentifier(), info.identifier());
1375 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1376 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1377
1378 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
1379 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
1380 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to create an index without an in-progress transaction"_s };
1381
1382 if (transaction->mode() != IDBTransactionMode::Versionchange) {
1383 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to create an index in a non-version-change transaction");
1384 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to create an index in a non-version-change transaction"_s };
1385 }
1386
1387 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> keyPathBlob = serializeIDBKeyPath(info.keyPath());
1388 if (!keyPathBlob) {
1389 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize IDBKeyPath to save in database");
1390 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize IDBKeyPath to create index in database"_s };
1391 }
1392
1393 {
1394 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::CreateIndexInfo, "INSERT INTO IndexInfo VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?);"_s);
1395 if (!sql
1396 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1397 || sql->bindText(2, info.name()) != SQLITE_OK
1398 || sql->bindInt64(3, info.objectStoreIdentifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1399 || sql->bindBlob(4, *keyPathBlob) != SQLITE_OK
1400 || sql->bindInt(5, info.unique()) != SQLITE_OK
1401 || sql->bindInt(6, info.multiEntry()) != SQLITE_OK
1402 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1403 LOG_ERROR("Could not add index '%s' to IndexInfo table (%i) - %s", info.name().utf8().data(), m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1404 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to create index in database"_s };
1405 }
1406 }
1407
1408 // Write index records for any records that already exist in this object store.
1409
1410 auto cursor = transaction->maybeOpenBackingStoreCursor(info.objectStoreIdentifier(), 0, IDBKeyRangeData::allKeys());
1411
1412 if (!cursor) {
1413 LOG_ERROR("Cannot open cursor to populate indexes in database");
1414 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to populate indexes in database"_s };
1415 }
1416
1417 while (!cursor->currentKey().isNull()) {
1418 auto& key = cursor->currentKey();
1419 auto value = cursor->currentValue();
1420 ThreadSafeDataBuffer valueBuffer = value.data();
1421
1422 ASSERT(cursor->currentRecordRowID());
1423
1424 auto* objectStoreInfo = infoForObjectStore(info.objectStoreIdentifier());
1425 ASSERT(objectStoreInfo);
1426 IDBError error = updateOneIndexForAddRecord(*objectStoreInfo, info, key, valueBuffer, cursor->currentRecordRowID());
1427 if (!error.isNull()) {
1428 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteIndexInfo, "DELETE FROM IndexInfo WHERE id = ? AND objectStoreID = ?;"_s);
1429 if (!sql
1430 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1431 || sql->bindInt64(2, info.objectStoreIdentifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1432 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1433 LOG_ERROR("Index creation failed due to uniqueness constraint failure, but there was an error deleting the Index record from the database");
1434 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Index creation failed due to uniqueness constraint failure, but there was an error deleting the Index record from the database"_s };
1435 }
1436
1437 return error;
1438 }
1439
1440 if (!cursor->advance(1)) {
1441 LOG_ERROR("Error advancing cursor while indexing existing records for new index.");
1442 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error advancing cursor while indexing existing records for new index"_s };
1443 }
1444 }
1445
1446 ASSERT(m_databaseInfo);
1447 if (!m_databaseInfo) {
1448 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(IndexedDB, "%p - SQLiteIDBBackingStore::clearObjectStore: m_databaseInfo is null", this);
1449 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Database info is invalid"_s };
1450 }
1451
1452 auto* objectStore = m_databaseInfo->infoForExistingObjectStore(info.objectStoreIdentifier());
1453 ASSERT(objectStore);
1454 objectStore->addExistingIndex(info);
1455 m_databaseInfo->setMaxIndexID(info.identifier());
1456
1457 return IDBError { };
1458}

1460IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::uncheckedHasIndexRecord(const IDBIndexInfo& info, const IDBKeyData& indexKey, bool& hasRecord)
1461{
1462 hasRecord = false;
1463
1464 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> indexKeyBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(indexKey);
1465 if (!indexKeyBuffer) {
1466 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize index key to be stored in the database");
1467 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize IDBKey to check for index record in database"_s };
1468 }
1469
1470 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::HasIndexRecord, "SELECT rowid FROM IndexRecords WHERE indexID = ? AND key = CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
1471 if (!sql
1472 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1473 || sql->bindBlob(2, *indexKeyBuffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
1474 LOG_ERROR("Error checking for index record in database");
1475 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error checking for index record in database"_s };
1476 }
1477
1478 int sqlResult = sql->step();
1479 if (sqlResult == SQLITE_OK || sqlResult == SQLITE_DONE)
1480 return IDBError { };
1481
1482 if (sqlResult != SQLITE_ROW) {
1483 // There was an error fetching the record from the database.
1484 LOG_ERROR("Could not check if key exists in index (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1485 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error checking for existence of IDBKey in index"_s };
1486 }
1487
1488 hasRecord = true;
1489 return IDBError { };
1490}
1491
1492IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::uncheckedPutIndexKey(const IDBIndexInfo& info, const IDBKeyData& key, const IndexKey& indexKey, int64_t recordID)
1493{
1494 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::uncheckedPutIndexKey - (%" PRIu64 ") %s, %s", info.identifier(), key.loggingString().utf8().data(), indexKey.asOneKey().loggingString().utf8().data());
1495
1496 Vector<IDBKeyData> indexKeys;
1497 if (info.multiEntry())
1498 indexKeys = indexKey.multiEntry();
1499 else
1500 indexKeys.append(indexKey.asOneKey());
1501
1502 if (info.unique()) {
1503 bool hasRecord;
1504 IDBError error;
1505 for (auto& indexKey : indexKeys) {
1506 if (!indexKey.isValid())
1507 continue;
1508 error = uncheckedHasIndexRecord(info, indexKey, hasRecord);
1509 if (!error.isNull())
1510 return error;
1511 if (hasRecord)
1512 return IDBError(ConstraintError);
1513 }
1514 }
1515
1516 for (auto& indexKey : indexKeys) {
1517 if (!indexKey.isValid())
1518 continue;
1519 auto error = uncheckedPutIndexRecord(info.objectStoreIdentifier(), info.identifier(), key, indexKey, recordID);
1520 if (!error.isNull()) {
1521 LOG_ERROR("Unable to put index record for newly created index");
1522 return error;
1523 }
1524 }
1525
1526 return IDBError { };
1527}

1530{
1531 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::uncheckedPutIndexRecord - %s, %s", keyValue.loggingString().utf8().data(), indexKey.loggingString().utf8().data());

1555 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error putting index record into database"_s };
1556 }
1557 }
1558
1559 return IDBError { };

1687
1688IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteUnusedBlobFileRecords(SQLiteIDBTransaction& transaction)
1689{
1690 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteUnusedBlobFileRecords");
1691
1692 // Gather the set of blob URLs and filenames that are no longer in use.
1693 HashSet<String> removedBlobFilenames;
1694 {
1695 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetUnusedBlobFilenames, "SELECT fileName FROM BlobFiles WHERE blobURL NOT IN (SELECT blobURL FROM BlobRecords)"_s);
1696
1697 if (!sql) {
1698 LOG_ERROR("Error deleting stored blobs (%i) (Could not gather unused blobURLs) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1699 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error deleting stored blobs"_s };
1700 }
1701
1702 int result = sql->step();
1703 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
1704 removedBlobFilenames.add(sql->columnText(0));
1705 result = sql->step();
1706 }
1707
1708 if (result != SQLITE_DONE) {
1709 LOG_ERROR("Error deleting stored blobs (%i) (Could not gather unused blobURLs) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1710 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error deleting stored blobs"_s };
1711 }
1712 }
1713
1714 // Remove the blob records that are no longer in use.
1715 if (!removedBlobFilenames.isEmpty()) {
1716 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteUnusedBlobs, "DELETE FROM BlobFiles WHERE blobURL NOT IN (SELECT blobURL FROM BlobRecords)"_s);
1717
1718 if (!sql
1719 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1720 LOG_ERROR("Error deleting stored blobs (%i) (Could not delete blobFile records) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1721 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error deleting stored blobs"_s };
1722 }
1723 }
1724
1725 for (auto& file : removedBlobFilenames)
1726 transaction.addRemovedBlobFile(file);
1727
1728 return IDBError { };
1729}
1730
1731IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteRecord(SQLiteIDBTransaction& transaction, int64_t objectStoreID, const IDBKeyData& keyData)
1732{
1733 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteRecord - key %s, object store %" PRIu64, keyData.loggingString().utf8().data(), objectStoreID);
1734
1735 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1736 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1737 ASSERT(transaction.inProgress());
1738 ASSERT(transaction.mode() != IDBTransactionMode::Readonly);
1739 UNUSED_PARAM(transaction);
1740
1741 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> keyBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(keyData);
1742 if (!keyBuffer) {
1743 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize IDBKeyData to be removed from the database");
1744 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize IDBKeyData to be removed from the database"_s };
1745 }
1746
1747 // Get the record ID and value.
1748 int64_t recordID;
1749 ThreadSafeDataBuffer value;
1750 {
1751 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetObjectStoreRecord, "SELECT recordID, value FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key = CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
1752
1753 if (!sql
1754 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreID) != SQLITE_OK
1755 || sql->bindBlob(2, *keyBuffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
1756 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete record from object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1757 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to delete record from object store"_s };
1758 }
1759
1760 int result = sql->step();
1761
1762 // If there's no record ID, there's no record to delete.
1763 if (result == SQLITE_DONE)
1764 return IDBError { };
1765
1766 if (result != SQLITE_ROW) {
1767 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete record from object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) (unable to fetch record ID) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1768 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to delete record from object store"_s };
1769 }
1770
1771 recordID = sql->columnInt64(0);
1772 value = ThreadSafeDataBuffer::create(sql->columnBlob(1));
1773 }
1774
1775 if (recordID < 1) {
1776 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete record from object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) (record ID is invalid) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1777 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to delete record from object store"_s };
1778 }
1779
1780 // Delete the blob records for this object store record.
1781 {
1782 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteBlobRecord, "DELETE FROM BlobRecords WHERE objectStoreRow = ?;"_s);
1783
1784 if (!sql
1785 || sql->bindInt64(1, recordID) != SQLITE_OK
1786 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1787 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete record from object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) (Could not delete BlobRecords records) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1788 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to delete record from object store"_s };
1789 }
1790 }
1791
1792 auto error = deleteUnusedBlobFileRecords(transaction);
1793 if (!error.isNull())
1794 return error;
1795
1796 // Delete record from object store
1797 {
1798 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreRecord, "DELETE FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key = CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
1799
1800 if (!sql
1801 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreID) != SQLITE_OK
1802 || sql->bindBlob(2, *keyBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
1803 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1804 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete record from object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1805 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to delete record from object store"_s };
1806 }
1807 }
1808
1809 // Delete record from indexes store
1810 {
1811 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreIndexRecord, "DELETE FROM IndexRecords WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND objectStoreRecordID = ?;"_s);
1812
1813 if (!sql
1814 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreID) != SQLITE_OK
1815 || sql->bindInt64(2, recordID) != SQLITE_OK
1816 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1817 LOG_ERROR("Could not delete record from indexes for object store %" PRIi64 " (%i) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1818 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to delete index entries for object store record"_s };
1819 }
1820 }
1821
1822 return IDBError { };
1823}
1824
1825IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteRange(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, uint64_t objectStoreID, const IDBKeyRangeData& keyRange)
1826{
1827 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteRange - range %s, object store %" PRIu64, keyRange.loggingString().utf8().data(), objectStoreID);
1828
1829 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1830 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1831
1832 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
1833 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
1834 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to delete range from database without an in-progress transaction"_s };
1835
1836 if (transaction->mode() == IDBTransactionMode::Readonly) {
1837 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to delete records from an object store in a read-only transaction");
1838 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to delete records from an object store in a read-only transaction"_s };
1839 }
1840
1841 // If the range to delete is exactly one key we can delete it right now.
1842 if (keyRange.isExactlyOneKey()) {
1843 auto error = deleteRecord(*transaction, objectStoreID, keyRange.lowerKey);
1844 if (!error.isNull()) {
1845 LOG_ERROR("Failed to delete record for key '%s'", keyRange.lowerKey.loggingString().utf8().data());
1846 return error;
1847 }
1848
1849 transaction->notifyCursorsOfChanges(objectStoreID);
1850
1851 return IDBError { };
1852 }
1853
1854 auto cursor = transaction->maybeOpenBackingStoreCursor(objectStoreID, 0, keyRange);
1855 if (!cursor) {
1856 LOG_ERROR("Cannot open cursor to delete range of records from the database");
1857 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Cannot open cursor to delete range of records from the database"_s };
1858 }
1859
1860 Vector<IDBKeyData> keys;
1861 while (!cursor->didComplete() && !cursor->didError()) {
1862 keys.append(cursor->currentKey());
1863 cursor->advance(1);
1864 }
1865
1866 if (cursor->didError()) {
1867 LOG_ERROR("Cursor failed while accumulating range of records from the database");
1868 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Cursor failed while accumulating range of records from the database"_s };
1869 }
1870
1871 IDBError error;
1872 for (auto& key : keys) {
1873 error = deleteRecord(*transaction, objectStoreID, key);
1874 if (!error.isNull()) {
1875 LOG_ERROR("deleteRange: Error deleting keys in range");
1876 break;
1877 }
1878 }
1879
1880 transaction->notifyCursorsOfChanges(objectStoreID);
1881
1882 return error;
1883}
1884
1885IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::updateOneIndexForAddRecord(IDBObjectStoreInfo& objectStoreInfo, const IDBIndexInfo& info, const IDBKeyData& key, const ThreadSafeDataBuffer& value, int64_t recordID)
1886{
1887 std::optional<IndexKey> resultIndexKey;
1888 callOnIDBSerializationThreadAndWait([objectStoreInfo = objectStoreInfo.isolatedCopy(), info = info.isolatedCopy(), key = key.isolatedCopy(), value, &resultIndexKey](auto& globalObject) {
1889 auto jsValue = deserializeIDBValueToJSValue(globalObject, value);
1890 if (jsValue.isUndefinedOrNull())
1891 return;
1892
1893 IndexKey indexKey;
1894 generateIndexKeyForValue(globalObject, info, jsValue, indexKey, objectStoreInfo.keyPath(), key);
1895 resultIndexKey = indexKey.isolatedCopy();
1896 });
1897
1898 if (!resultIndexKey)
1899 return IDBError { };
1900
1901 if (resultIndexKey->isNull())
1902 return IDBError { };
1903
1904 return uncheckedPutIndexKey(info, key, *resultIndexKey, recordID);
1905}
1906
1907IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::updateAllIndexesForAddRecord(const IDBObjectStoreInfo& info, const IDBKeyData& key, const IndexIDToIndexKeyMap& indexKeys, int64_t recordID)
1908{
1909 IDBError error;
1910 const auto& indexMap = info.indexMap();
1911 bool anyRecordsSucceeded = false;
1912
1913 for (const auto& entry : indexKeys) {
1914 auto indexIterator = indexMap.find(entry.key);
1915 ASSERT(indexIterator != indexMap.end());
1916
1917 if (indexIterator == indexMap.end()) {
1918 error = IDBError { InvalidStateError, "Missing index metadata" };
1919 break;
1920 }
1921
1922 error = uncheckedPutIndexKey(indexIterator->value, key, entry.value, recordID);
1923 if (!error.isNull())
1924 break;
1925
1926 anyRecordsSucceeded = true;
1927 }
1928
1929 if (!error.isNull() && anyRecordsSucceeded) {
1930 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreIndexRecord, "DELETE FROM IndexRecords WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND objectStoreRecordID = ?;"_s);
1931
1932 if (!sql
1933 || sql->bindInt64(1, info.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1934 || sql->bindInt64(2, recordID) != SQLITE_OK
1935 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1936 LOG_ERROR("Adding one Index record failed, but failed to remove all others that previously succeeded");
1937 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Adding one Index record failed, but failed to remove all others that previously succeeded"_s };
1938 }
1939 }
1940
1941 return error;
1942}
1943
1944IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::addRecord(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, const IDBObjectStoreInfo& objectStoreInfo, const IDBKeyData& keyData, const IndexIDToIndexKeyMap& indexKeys, const IDBValue& value)
1945{
1946 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::addRecord - key %s, object store %" PRIu64, keyData.loggingString().utf8().data(), objectStoreInfo.identifier());
1947
1948 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
1949 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
1950 ASSERT(value.data().data());
1951 ASSERT(value.blobURLs().size() == value.blobFilePaths().size());
1952
1953 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
1954 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
1955 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to store a record in an object store without an in-progress transaction"_s };
1956
1957 if (transaction->mode() == IDBTransactionMode::Readonly) {
1958 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to store a record in an object store in a read-only transaction");
1959 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to store a record in an object store in a read-only transaction"_s };
1960 }
1961
1962 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> keyBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(keyData);
1963 if (!keyBuffer) {
1964 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize IDBKey to be stored in an object store");
1965 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize IDBKey to be stored in an object store"_s };
1966 }
1967
1968 int64_t recordID = 0;
1969 {
1970 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::AddObjectStoreRecord, "INSERT INTO Records VALUES (?, CAST(? AS TEXT), ?, NULL);"_s);
1971 if (!sql
1972 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreInfo.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1973 || sql->bindBlob(2, *keyBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
1974 || sql->bindBlob(3, *value.data().data()) != SQLITE_OK
1975 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1976 LOG_ERROR("Could not put record for object store %" PRIi64 " in Records table (%i) - %s", objectStoreInfo.identifier(), m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
1977 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to store record in object store"_s };
1978 }
1979
1980 recordID = m_sqliteDB->lastInsertRowID();
1981 }
1982
1983 auto error = updateAllIndexesForAddRecord(objectStoreInfo, keyData, indexKeys, recordID);
1984
1985 if (!error.isNull()) {
1986 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::DeleteObjectStoreRecord, "DELETE FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key = CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
1987 if (!sql
1988 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreInfo.identifier()) != SQLITE_OK
1989 || sql->bindBlob(2, *keyBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
1990 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
1991 LOG_ERROR("Indexing new object store record failed, but unable to remove the object store record itself");
1992 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Indexing new object store record failed, but unable to remove the object store record itself"_s };
1993 }
1994
1995 return error;
1996 }
1997
1998 const Vector<String>& blobURLs = value.blobURLs();
1999 const Vector<String>& blobFiles = value.blobFilePaths();
2000 for (size_t i = 0; i < blobURLs.size(); ++i) {
2001 auto& url = blobURLs[i];
2002 {
2003 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::AddBlobRecord, "INSERT INTO BlobRecords VALUES (?, ?);"_s);
2004 if (!sql
2005 || sql->bindInt64(1, recordID) != SQLITE_OK
2006 || sql->bindText(2, url) != SQLITE_OK
2007 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
2008 LOG_ERROR("Unable to record Blob record in database");
2009 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to record Blob record in database"_s };
2010 }
2011 }
2012 int64_t potentialFileNameInteger = m_sqliteDB->lastInsertRowID();
2013
2014 // If we already have a file for this blobURL, nothing left to do.
2015 {
2016 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::BlobFilenameForBlobURL, "SELECT fileName FROM BlobFiles WHERE blobURL = ?;"_s);
2017 if (!sql
2018 || sql->bindText(1, url) != SQLITE_OK) {
2019 LOG_ERROR("Unable to examine Blob filenames in database");
2020 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to examine Blob filenames in database"_s };
2021 }
2022
2023 int result = sql->step();
2024 if (result != SQLITE_ROW && result != SQLITE_DONE) {
2025 LOG_ERROR("Unable to examine Blob filenames in database");
2026 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to examine Blob filenames in database"_s };
2027 }
2028
2029 if (result == SQLITE_ROW)
2030 continue;
2031 }
2032
2033 // We don't already have a file for this blobURL, so commit our file as a unique filename
2034 auto storedFilename = makeString(potentialFileNameInteger, ".blob");
2035 {
2036 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::AddBlobFilename, "INSERT INTO BlobFiles VALUES (?, ?);"_s);
2037 if (!sql
2038 || sql->bindText(1, url) != SQLITE_OK
2039 || sql->bindText(2, storedFilename) != SQLITE_OK
2040 || sql->step() != SQLITE_DONE) {
2041 LOG_ERROR("Unable to record Blob file record in database");
2042 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to record Blob file record in database"_s };
2043 }
2044 }
2045
2046 transaction->addBlobFile(blobFiles[i], storedFilename);
2047 }
2048
2049 transaction->notifyCursorsOfChanges(objectStoreInfo.identifier());
2050
2051 return error;
2052}
2053
2054IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getBlobRecordsForObjectStoreRecord(int64_t objectStoreRecord, Vector<String>& blobURLs, Vector<String>& blobFilePaths)
2055{
2056 ASSERT(objectStoreRecord);
2057
2058 HashSet<String> blobURLSet;
2059 {
2060 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetBlobURL, "SELECT blobURL FROM BlobRecords WHERE objectStoreRow = ?"_s);
2061 if (!sql
2062 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreRecord) != SQLITE_OK) {
2063 LOG_ERROR("Could not prepare statement to fetch blob URLs for object store record (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2064 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to look up blobURL records in object store by key range"_s };
2065 }
2066
2067 int sqlResult = sql->step();
2068 if (sqlResult == SQLITE_OK || sqlResult == SQLITE_DONE) {
2069 // There are no blobURLs in the database for this object store record.
2070 return IDBError { };
2071 }
2072
2073 while (sqlResult == SQLITE_ROW) {
2074 blobURLSet.add(sql->columnText(0));
2075 sqlResult = sql->step();
2076 }
2077
2078 if (sqlResult != SQLITE_DONE) {
2079 LOG_ERROR("Could not fetch blob URLs for object store record (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2080 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to look up blobURL records in object store by key range"_s };
2081 }
2082 }
2083
2084 ASSERT(!blobURLSet.isEmpty());
2085 for (auto& blobURL : blobURLSet) {
2086 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::BlobFilenameForBlobURL, "SELECT fileName FROM BlobFiles WHERE blobURL = ?;"_s);
2087 if (!sql
2088 || sql->bindText(1, blobURL) != SQLITE_OK) {
2089 LOG_ERROR("Could not prepare statement to fetch blob filename for object store record (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2090 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to look up blobURL records in object store by key range"_s };
2091 }
2092
2093 if (sql->step() != SQLITE_ROW) {
2094 LOG_ERROR("Entry for blob filename for blob url %s does not exist (%i) - %s", blobURL.utf8().data(), m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2095 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to look up blobURL records in object store by key range"_s };
2096 }
2097
2098 blobURLs.append(blobURL);
2099
2100 String fileName = sql->columnText(0);
2101 blobFilePaths.append(FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(m_databaseDirectory, fileName));
2102 }
2103 return IDBError { };
2104}
2105
2106IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getRecord(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, uint64_t objectStoreID, const IDBKeyRangeData& keyRange, IDBGetRecordDataType type, IDBGetResult& resultValue)
2107{
2108 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getRecord - key range %s, object store %" PRIu64, keyRange.loggingString().utf8().data(), objectStoreID);
2109
2110 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
2111 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
2112
2113 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
2114 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
2115 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to get a record from database without an in-progress transaction"_s };
2116
2117 auto* objectStoreInfo = infoForObjectStore(objectStoreID);
2118 if (!objectStoreInfo)
2119 return IDBError { InvalidStateError, "Object store cannot be found in the backing store"_s };
2120
2121 auto key = keyRange.lowerKey;
2122 if (key.isNull())
2123 key = IDBKeyData::minimum();
2124 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> lowerBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(key);
2125 if (!lowerBuffer) {
2126 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize lower IDBKey in lookup range");
2127 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize lower IDBKey in lookup range"_s };
2128 }
2129
2130 key = keyRange.upperKey;
2131 if (key.isNull())
2132 key = IDBKeyData::maximum();
2133 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> upperBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(key);
2134 if (!upperBuffer) {
2135 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize upper IDBKey in lookup range");
2136 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize upper IDBKey in lookup range"_s };
2137 }
2138
2139 int64_t recordID = 0;
2140 ThreadSafeDataBuffer keyResultBuffer, valueResultBuffer;
2141 {
2142 SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope sql;
2143
2144 switch (type) {
2145 case IDBGetRecordDataType::KeyAndValue:
2146 if (keyRange.lowerOpen) {
2147 if (keyRange.upperOpen)
2148 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetValueRecordsLowerOpenUpperOpen, "SELECT key, value, ROWID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2149 else
2150 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetValueRecordsLowerOpenUpperClosed, "SELECT key, value, ROWID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2151 } else {
2152 if (keyRange.upperOpen)
2153 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetValueRecordsLowerClosedUpperOpen, "SELECT key, value, ROWID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2154 else
2155 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetValueRecordsLowerClosedUpperClosed, "SELECT key, value, ROWID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2156 }
2157 break;
2158 case IDBGetRecordDataType::KeyOnly:
2159 if (keyRange.lowerOpen) {
2160 if (keyRange.upperOpen)
2161 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetKeyRecordsLowerOpenUpperOpen, "SELECT key FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2162 else
2163 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetKeyRecordsLowerOpenUpperClosed, "SELECT key FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2164 } else {
2165 if (keyRange.upperOpen)
2166 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetKeyRecordsLowerClosedUpperOpen, "SELECT key FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2167 else
2168 sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetKeyRecordsLowerClosedUpperClosed, "SELECT key FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2169 }
2170 }
2171
2172 if (!sql
2173 || sql->bindInt64(1, objectStoreID) != SQLITE_OK
2174 || sql->bindBlob(2, *lowerBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
2175 || sql->bindBlob(3, *upperBuffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
2176 LOG_ERROR("Could not get key range record from object store %" PRIi64 " from Records table (%i) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2177 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to look up record in object store by key range"_s };
2178 }
2179
2180 int sqlResult = sql->step();
2181
2182 if (sqlResult == SQLITE_OK || sqlResult == SQLITE_DONE) {
2183 // There was no record for the key in the database.
2184 return IDBError { };
2185 }
2186 if (sqlResult != SQLITE_ROW) {
2187 // There was an error fetching the record from the database.
2188 LOG_ERROR("Could not get record from object store %" PRIi64 " from Records table (%i) - %s", objectStoreID, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2189 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error looking up record in object store by key range"_s };
2190 }
2191
2192 keyResultBuffer = ThreadSafeDataBuffer::create(sql->columnBlob(0));
2193
2194 if (type == IDBGetRecordDataType::KeyAndValue) {
2195 valueResultBuffer = ThreadSafeDataBuffer::create(sql->columnBlob(1));
2196 recordID = sql->columnInt64(2);
2197 }
2198 }
2199
2200 auto* keyVector = keyResultBuffer.data();
2201 if (!keyVector) {
2202 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key data from database for IDBObjectStore");
2203 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error extracting key data from database executing IDBObjectStore get"_s };
2204 }
2205
2206 IDBKeyData keyData;
2207 if (!deserializeIDBKeyData(keyVector->data(), keyVector->size(), keyData)) {
2208 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key data from database for IDBObjectStore");
2209 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error extracting key data from database executing IDBObjectStore get"_s };
2210 }
2211
2212 if (type == IDBGetRecordDataType::KeyOnly) {
2213 resultValue = { keyData };
2214 return IDBError { };
2215 }
2216
2217 ASSERT(recordID);
2218 Vector<String> blobURLs, blobFilePaths;
2219 auto error = getBlobRecordsForObjectStoreRecord(recordID, blobURLs, blobFilePaths);
2220 ASSERT(blobURLs.size() == blobFilePaths.size());
2221
2222 if (!error.isNull())
2223 return error;
2224
2225 resultValue = { keyData, { valueResultBuffer, WTFMove(blobURLs), WTFMove(blobFilePaths) }, objectStoreInfo->keyPath() };
2226 return IDBError { };
2227}

2229IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getAllRecords(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, const IDBGetAllRecordsData& getAllRecordsData, IDBGetAllResult& result)
2230{
2231 return getAllRecordsData.indexIdentifier ? getAllIndexRecords(transactionIdentifier, getAllRecordsData, result) : getAllObjectStoreRecords(transactionIdentifier, getAllRecordsData, result);
2232}
2233
2234SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope SQLiteIDBBackingStore::cachedStatementForGetAllObjectStoreRecords(const IDBGetAllRecordsData& getAllRecordsData)
2235{
2236 if (getAllRecordsData.getAllType == IndexedDB::GetAllType::Keys) {
2237 if (getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.lowerOpen) {
2238 if (getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.upperOpen)

2240 return cachedStatement(SQL::GetAllKeyRecordsLowerOpenUpperClosed, "SELECT key FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2241 }
2242
2243 if (getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.upperOpen)

2245 return cachedStatement(SQL::GetAllKeyRecordsLowerClosedUpperClosed, "SELECT key FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2246 }

2248 if (getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.lowerOpen) {
2249 if (getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.upperOpen)
2250 return cachedStatement(SQL::GetValueRecordsLowerOpenUpperOpen, "SELECT key, value, ROWID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2251 return cachedStatement(SQL::GetValueRecordsLowerOpenUpperClosed, "SELECT key, value, ROWID FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY key;"_s);
2252 }

2259IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getAllObjectStoreRecords(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, const IDBGetAllRecordsData& getAllRecordsData, IDBGetAllResult& result)
2260{
2261 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getAllObjectStoreRecords");
2262
2263 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
2264 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
2265
2266 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
2267 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
2268 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to get records from database without an in-progress transaction"_s };
2269
2270 auto key = getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.lowerKey;
2271 if (key.isNull())
2272 key = IDBKeyData::minimum();
2273 auto lowerBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(key);
2274 if (!lowerBuffer) {
2275 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize lower IDBKey in lookup range");
2276 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize lower IDBKey in lookup range"_s };
2277 }
2278
2279 key = getAllRecordsData.keyRangeData.upperKey;
2280 if (key.isNull())
2281 key = IDBKeyData::maximum();
2282 auto upperBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(key);
2283 if (!upperBuffer) {
2284 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize upper IDBKey in lookup range");
2285 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize upper IDBKey in lookup range"_s };
2286 }
2287
2288 auto sql = cachedStatementForGetAllObjectStoreRecords(getAllRecordsData);
2289 if (!sql
2290 || sql->bindInt64(1, getAllRecordsData.objectStoreIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK
2291 || sql->bindBlob(2, *lowerBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
2292 || sql->bindBlob(3, *upperBuffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
2293 LOG_ERROR("Could not get key range record from object store %" PRIi64 " from Records table (%i) - %s", getAllRecordsData.objectStoreIdentifier, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2294 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Failed to look up record in object store by key range"_s };
2295 }
2296
2297 auto* objectStoreInfo = infoForObjectStore(getAllRecordsData.objectStoreIdentifier);
2298 ASSERT(objectStoreInfo);
2299 result = { getAllRecordsData.getAllType, objectStoreInfo->keyPath() };
2300
2301 uint32_t targetResults;
2302 if (getAllRecordsData.count && getAllRecordsData.count.value())
2303 targetResults = getAllRecordsData.count.value();
2304 else
2305 targetResults = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
2306
2307 int sqlResult = sql->step();
2308 uint32_t returnedResults = 0;
2309
2310 while (sqlResult == SQLITE_ROW && returnedResults < targetResults) {
2311 auto keyBufferSpan = sql->columnBlobAsSpan(0);
2312 IDBKeyData keyData;
2313 if (!deserializeIDBKeyData(keyBufferSpan.data(), keyBufferSpan.size(), keyData)) {
2314 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key data from database while getting all records");
2315 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to deserialize key data while getting all records"_s };
2316 }
2317 result.addKey(WTFMove(keyData));
2318
2319 if (getAllRecordsData.getAllType == IndexedDB::GetAllType::Values) {
2320 ThreadSafeDataBuffer valueResultBuffer = ThreadSafeDataBuffer::create(sql->columnBlob(1));
2321
2322 auto recordID = sql->columnInt64(2);
2323
2324 ASSERT(recordID);
2325 Vector<String> blobURLs, blobFilePaths;
2326 auto error = getBlobRecordsForObjectStoreRecord(recordID, blobURLs, blobFilePaths);
2327 ASSERT(blobURLs.size() == blobFilePaths.size());
2328
2329 if (!error.isNull())
2330 return error;
2331
2332 result.addValue({ valueResultBuffer, WTFMove(blobURLs), WTFMove(blobFilePaths) });
2333 }
2334
2335 ++returnedResults;
2336 sqlResult = sql->step();
2337 }
2338
2339 if (sqlResult == SQLITE_OK || sqlResult == SQLITE_DONE || sqlResult == SQLITE_ROW) {
2340 // Finished getting results
2341 return IDBError { };
2342 }
2343
2344 // There was an error fetching records from the database.
2345 LOG_ERROR("Could not get record from object store %" PRIi64 " from Records table (%i) - %s", getAllRecordsData.objectStoreIdentifier, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2346 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Error looking up record in object store by key range"_s };
2347}

2353 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);

2357 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())

2397IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getIndexRecord(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, uint64_t objectStoreID, uint64_t indexID, IndexedDB::IndexRecordType type, const IDBKeyRangeData& range, IDBGetResult& getResult)
2398{
2399 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getIndexRecord - %s", range.loggingString().utf8().data());
2400
2401 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
