2437IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::uncheckedGetIndexRecordForOneKey(int64_t indexID, int64_t objectStoreID, IndexedDB::IndexRecordType type, const IDBKeyData& key, IDBGetResult& getResult)
2438{
2439 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::uncheckedGetIndexRecordForOneKey");
2440
2441 ASSERT(key.isValid() && key.type() != IndexedDB::KeyType::Max && key.type() != IndexedDB::KeyType::Min);
2442
2443 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> buffer = serializeIDBKeyData(key);
2444 if (!buffer) {
2445 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize IDBKey to look up one index record");
2446 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize IDBKey to look up one index record"_s };
2447 }
2448
2449 auto sql = cachedStatement(SQL::GetIndexRecordForOneKey, "SELECT IndexRecords.value, Records.value, Records.recordID FROM Records INNER JOIN IndexRecords ON Records.objectStoreID = IndexRecords.objectStoreID AND Records.recordID = IndexRecords.objectStoreRecordID WHERE IndexRecords.indexID = ? AND IndexRecords.key = CAST(? AS TEXT) ORDER BY IndexRecords.key, IndexRecords.value"_s);
2450
2451 if (!sql
2452 || sql->bindInt64(1, indexID) != SQLITE_OK
2453 || sql->bindBlob(2, *buffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
2454 LOG_ERROR("Unable to lookup index record in database");
2455 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to lookup index record in database"_s };
2456 }
2457
2458 int result = sql->step();
2459 if (result != SQLITE_ROW && result != SQLITE_DONE) {
2460 LOG_ERROR("Unable to lookup index record in database");
2461 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to lookup index record in database"_s };
2462 }
2463
2464 if (result == SQLITE_DONE)
2465 return IDBError { };
2466
2467 IDBKeyData objectStoreKey;
2468 auto keySpan = sql->columnBlobAsSpan(0);
2469
2470 if (!deserializeIDBKeyData(keySpan.data(), keySpan.size(), objectStoreKey)) {
2471 LOG_ERROR("Unable to deserialize key looking up index record in database");
2472 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to deserialize key looking up index record in database"_s };
2473 }
2474
2475 if (type == IndexedDB::IndexRecordType::Key) {
2476 getResult = { objectStoreKey };
2477 return IDBError { };
2478 }
2479
2480 auto valueVector = sql->columnBlob(1);
2481 int64_t recordID = sql->columnInt64(2);
2482 Vector<String> blobURLs, blobFilePaths;
2483 auto error = getBlobRecordsForObjectStoreRecord(recordID, blobURLs, blobFilePaths);
2484 ASSERT(blobURLs.size() == blobFilePaths.size());
2485
2486 if (!error.isNull())
2487 return error;
2488
2489 auto* objectStoreInfo = infoForObjectStore(objectStoreID);
2490 ASSERT(objectStoreInfo);
2491 getResult = { objectStoreKey, objectStoreKey, { ThreadSafeDataBuffer::create(WTFMove(valueVector)), WTFMove(blobURLs), WTFMove(blobFilePaths) }, objectStoreInfo->keyPath() };
2492 return IDBError { };
2493}

2495IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getCount(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, uint64_t objectStoreIdentifier, uint64_t indexIdentifier, const IDBKeyRangeData& range, uint64_t& outCount)
2496{
2497 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::getCount - object store %" PRIu64, objectStoreIdentifier);
2498 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
2499 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
2500
2501 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
2502 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
2503 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to get count from database without an in-progress transaction"_s };
2504
2505 outCount = 0;
2506
2507 auto lowerKey = range.lowerKey.isNull() ? IDBKeyData::minimum() : range.lowerKey;
2508 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> lowerBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(lowerKey);
2509 if (!lowerBuffer) {
2510 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize lower IDBKey in lookup range");
2511 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize lower IDBKey in lookup range for count operation"_s };
2512 }
2513
2514 auto upperKey = range.upperKey.isNull() ? IDBKeyData::maximum() : range.upperKey;
2515 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> upperBuffer = serializeIDBKeyData(upperKey);
2516 if (!upperBuffer) {
2517 LOG_ERROR("Unable to serialize upper IDBKey in lookup range");
2518 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to serialize upper IDBKey in lookup range for count operation"_s };
2519 }
2520
2521 SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope statement;
2522
2523 if (!indexIdentifier) {
2524 if (range.lowerOpen && range.upperOpen)
2525 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountRecordsLowerOpenUpperOpen, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2526 else if (range.lowerOpen && !range.upperOpen)
2527 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountRecordsLowerOpenUpperClosed, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2528 else if (!range.lowerOpen && range.upperOpen)
2529 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountRecordsLowerClosedUpperOpen, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2530 else
2531 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountRecordsLowerClosedUpperClosed, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Records WHERE objectStoreID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2532
2533 if (!statement
2534 || statement->bindInt64(1, objectStoreIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK
2535 || statement->bindBlob(2, *lowerBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
2536 || statement->bindBlob(3, *upperBuffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
2537 LOG_ERROR("Could not count records in object store %" PRIi64 " from Records table (%i) - %s", objectStoreIdentifier, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2538 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to count records in object store due to binding failure"_s };
2539 }
2540 } else {
2541 if (range.lowerOpen && range.upperOpen)
2542 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountIndexRecordsLowerOpenUpperOpen, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM IndexRecords WHERE indexID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2543 else if (range.lowerOpen && !range.upperOpen)
2544 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountIndexRecordsLowerOpenUpperClosed, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM IndexRecords WHERE indexID = ? AND key > CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2545 else if (!range.lowerOpen && range.upperOpen)
2546 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountIndexRecordsLowerClosedUpperOpen, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM IndexRecords WHERE indexID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key < CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2547 else
2548 statement = cachedStatement(SQL::CountIndexRecordsLowerClosedUpperClosed, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM IndexRecords WHERE indexID = ? AND key >= CAST(? AS TEXT) AND key <= CAST(? AS TEXT);"_s);
2549
2550 if (!statement
2551 || statement->bindInt64(1, indexIdentifier) != SQLITE_OK
2552 || statement->bindBlob(2, *lowerBuffer) != SQLITE_OK
2553 || statement->bindBlob(3, *upperBuffer) != SQLITE_OK) {
2554 LOG_ERROR("Could not count records with index %" PRIi64 " from IndexRecords table (%i) - %s", indexIdentifier, m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2555 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to count records for index due to binding failure"_s };
2556 }
2557 }
2558
2559 if (statement->step() != SQLITE_ROW)
2560 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Unable to count records"_s };
2561
2562 outCount = statement->columnInt(0);
2563 return IDBError { };
2564}

2602IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::generateKeyNumber(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, uint64_t objectStoreID, uint64_t& generatedKey)
2603{
2604 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::generateKeyNumber");
2605
2606 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
2607 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
2608
2609 auto* transaction = m_transactions.get(transactionIdentifier);
2610 if (!transaction || !transaction->inProgress())
2611 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to generate key in database without an in-progress transaction"_s };
2612
2613 if (transaction->mode() == IDBTransactionMode::Readonly) {
2614 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to generate key in a read-only transaction");
2615 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to generate key in a read-only transaction"_s };
2616 }
2617
2618 uint64_t currentValue;
2619 auto error = uncheckedGetKeyGeneratorValue(objectStoreID, currentValue);
2620 if (!error.isNull())
2621 return error;
2622
2623 if (currentValue + 1 > maxGeneratorValue)
2624 return IDBError { ConstraintError, "Cannot generate new key value over 2^53 for object store operation" };
2625
2626 generatedKey = currentValue + 1;
2627 return uncheckedSetKeyGeneratorValue(objectStoreID, generatedKey);
2628}

2653
2654 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);

2656

2699
2700IDBError SQLiteIDBBackingStore::iterateCursor(const IDBResourceIdentifier& transactionIdentifier, const IDBResourceIdentifier& cursorIdentifier, const IDBIterateCursorData& data, IDBGetResult& result)
2701{
2702 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::iterateCursor");
2703
2704 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB);
2705 ASSERT(m_sqliteDB->isOpen());
2706
2707 auto* cursor = m_cursors.get(cursorIdentifier);
2708 if (!cursor) {
2709 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to iterate a cursor that doesn't exist");
2710 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to iterate a cursor that doesn't exist"_s };
2711 }
2712
2713 ASSERT_UNUSED(transactionIdentifier, cursor->transaction()->transactionIdentifier() == transactionIdentifier);
2714
2715 if (!cursor->transaction() || !cursor->transaction()->inProgress())
2716 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to iterate a cursor without an in-progress transaction"_s };
2717
2718 auto key = data.keyData;
2719 auto primaryKey = data.primaryKeyData;
2720 auto count = data.count;
2721
2722 if (key.isValid()) {
2723 if (!cursor->iterate(key, primaryKey)) {
2724 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to iterate cursor failed");
2725 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to iterate cursor failed"_s };
2726 }
2727 } else {
2728 ASSERT(!primaryKey.isValid());
2729 if (!count)
2730 count = 1;
2731 if (!cursor->advance(count)) {
2732 LOG_ERROR("Attempt to advance cursor failed");
2733 return IDBError { UnknownError, "Attempt to advance cursor failed"_s };
2734 }
2735 }
2736
2737 if (data.option == IndexedDB::CursorIterateOption::Reply) {
2738 auto* objectStoreInfo = infoForObjectStore(cursor->objectStoreID());
2739 ASSERT(objectStoreInfo);
2740
2741 bool shouldPrefetch = key.isNull() && primaryKey.isNull();
2742 if (shouldPrefetch)
2743 cursor->prefetch();
2744
2745 cursor->currentData(result, objectStoreInfo->keyPath(), shouldPrefetch ? SQLiteIDBCursor::ShouldIncludePrefetchedRecords::Yes : SQLiteIDBCursor::ShouldIncludePrefetchedRecords::No);
2746 }
2747
2748 return IDBError { };
2749}

2756
2757void SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteBackingStore()
2758{
2759 String databasePath = fullDatabasePath();
2760
2761 LOG(IndexedDB, "SQLiteIDBBackingStore::deleteBackingStore deleting file '%s' on disk", databasePath.utf8().data());
2762
2763 if (FileSystem::fileExists(databasePath) && !m_sqliteDB) {
2764 m_sqliteDB = makeUnique<SQLiteDatabase>();
2765 if (!m_sqliteDB->open(databasePath))
2766 closeSQLiteDB();
2767 }
2768
2769 if (m_sqliteDB) {
2770 Vector<String> blobFiles;
2771 {
2772 auto sql = m_sqliteDB->prepareStatement("SELECT fileName FROM BlobFiles;"_s);
2773 if (!sql)
2774 LOG_ERROR("Error preparing statement to get blob filenames (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2775 else {
2776 int result = sql->step();
2777 while (result == SQLITE_ROW) {
2778 blobFiles.append(sql->columnText(0));
2779 result = sql->step();
2780 }
2781
2782 if (result != SQLITE_DONE)
2783 LOG_ERROR("Error getting blob filenames (%i) - %s", m_sqliteDB->lastError(), m_sqliteDB->lastErrorMsg());
2784 }
2785 }
2786
2787 for (auto& file : blobFiles) {
2788 String blobPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(m_databaseDirectory, file);
2789 if (!FileSystem::deleteFile(blobPath))
2790 LOG_ERROR("Error deleting blob file '%s'", blobPath.utf8().data());
2791 }
2792
2793 closeSQLiteDB();
2794 }
2795
2796 SQLiteFileSystem::deleteDatabaseFile(databasePath);
2797 SQLiteFileSystem::deleteEmptyDatabaseDirectory(m_databaseDirectory);
2798 SQLiteFileSystem::deleteEmptyDatabaseDirectory(m_identifier.databaseDirectoryRelativeToRoot(m_databaseRootDirectory));
2799}

2804 m_cursors.remove(cursor.identifier());

2807SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope SQLiteIDBBackingStore::cachedStatement(SQLiteIDBBackingStore::SQL sql, ASCIILiteral query)
2808{
2809 if (sql >= SQL::Invalid) {
2810 LOG_ERROR("Invalid SQL statement ID passed to cachedStatement()");
2811 return SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope { };
2812 }
2813
2814 if (m_cachedStatements[static_cast<size_t>(sql)])
2815 return SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope { m_cachedStatements[static_cast<size_t>(sql)].get() };
2816
2817 if (m_sqliteDB) {
2818 auto statement = m_sqliteDB->prepareHeapStatement(query);
2819 if (statement)
2820 m_cachedStatements[static_cast<size_t>(sql)] = statement.value().moveToUniquePtr();
2821 }
2822
2823 return SQLiteStatementAutoResetScope { m_cachedStatements[static_cast<size_t>(sql)].get() };
2824}

2831void SQLiteIDBBackingStore::closeSQLiteDB()
2832{
2833 for (size_t i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(SQL::Invalid); ++i)
2834 m_cachedStatements[i] = nullptr;
2835
2836 if (m_sqliteDB)
2837 m_sqliteDB->close();
2838
2839 m_sqliteDB = nullptr;
2840}
